description:
BDC is a simple library for updating the DOM to match a javascript description.
Does not require JSX or a compilation step.<p><pre><code>    clobber(
      document.body,
      h(&quot;marquee&quot;, [
        h(&quot;span&quot;, {&quot;style&quot;: &quot;font-weight: bold&quot;}, &quot;Hello&quot;), &quot;, &quot;,
        h(&quot;blink&quot;, &quot;world&quot;), &quot;!&quot;,
      ]),
    );
</code></pre>
Very fast to first render, moderately slow on subsequent updates.<p>Prompted by the post on millionjs, which uses compiles user code to hit the same outrageously small size target.<p>Prompted by the post on millionjs, which uses compilation to hit the same outrageously small size target.

